exponentiate Q like this.

01:17:32.460 --> 01:17:38.700 align:middle line:84%
And then this operator
then generates--

01:17:38.700 --> 01:17:45.970 align:middle line:84%
when it acts on
phi, then generates

01:17:45.970 --> 01:17:47.380 align:middle line:90%
finite transformations.

01:17:47.380 --> 01:17:58.960 align:middle line:90%


01:17:58.960 --> 01:18:02.050 align:middle line:84%
So this takes you
to phi a prime--

01:18:02.050 --> 01:18:03.400 align:middle line:90%
the finite transformations.

01:18:03.400 --> 01:18:07.450 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, so in your
pset, for pset 2,

